1)@NotNull validates that the annotated property value is not null
2)@Size validates that the annotated property value has a size between min and max attr, can be applied to string,map,array
3)@Min validates that the annotated property has a value no smaller than the value attr
4)@Max validates that the annotated prop has a value no larger than the value attr
5)@Email validated that the annotated porp is a valid email address
6)@NotEmpty validates that prop is not null or empty; can be applied to string,collection,map or array values
7)@NotBlank can be applied only to text values and validates that the prop is not null or whitespace


spring boot uses hibernate validator as a validator internally
dependency used:
<dependency>
<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>
</dependency>